<p>The Mid-Cambridge area, including neighborhoods near MIT, features many triple-decker homes perfect for multi-zone ductless heat pump systems. North Cambridge residents often have larger lots with fewer shading issues, making solar installations more straightforward. West Cambridge's more suburban character includes newer construction that may already have modern HVAC systems but can benefit significantly from solar additions. Each neighborhood's tree canopy and building density should be evaluated for optimal solar panel placement and seasonal shading impacts.</p>

